{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> ἐξᾰμαρτ-άνω</b>, <br /> <i>future</i> -ήσομαι (<b>-ήσω</b>[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Hippocrates Medicus “Acut. (Sp.”) 13)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]:—<b>miss the mark, fail,</b> with <i>participle</i>, ἐ. παίοντες [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Institutio Cyri (Cyropaedia)” 2.1.16 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: <i>absolutely</i>, <b>miss one's aim,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Philoctetes” 95 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; opposed to κατορθοῦν, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Isocrates Orator 7.72. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> <b>err, do wrong,</b> <i>absolutely</i>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Prometheus Vinctus” 1039, etc.; τοῖς πᾶσι κοινόν ἐστι τοὐξ. 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Antigone” 1024, compare 4th-3rd c.BC: Menander Comicus 15.1D. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; opposed to εὖ ποιεῖν, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Lysias Orator 25.16; ἔς τινα 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 1.108, 5th c.BC: Lysias Orator 12.20; εἰς τοὺς οἰκέτας 5th-6th c.BC: Isocrates Orator 2.5; εἰς θεούς 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Prometheus Vinctus” 945; περί τινα 5th-6th c.BC: Isocrates Orator 4.110, 9.24 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἔν τινι in a thing, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Respublica” 336e; περὶ τὰ μέγιστα 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Anabasis” 5.7.33 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: with <i>participle</i>, ἐ. διατρίβων [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Cyr.” 3.3.56: with _accusative_ _cognate_, ἐ. τι\">Refs</a>] <b>commit</b> a <b>fault,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 3.145, 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Philoctetes” 1012, etc. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <i>passive</i>, <b>to be mismanaged, to be a fai